Looking at the code, users can override `defaultColDef` through the `agGridProps` prop. Here's how:

```tsx
<DataGridPanel
  meta={meta}
  data={data}
  agGridProps={{
    defaultColDef: {
      cellStyle: { 
        display: "flex", 
        justifyContent: "center", 
        alignItems: "center" 
      }
    }
  }}
/>
```

The `agGridProps` prop accepts any valid AG Grid React props (line 242), including `defaultColDef`. Since the component likely merges this with the internal `defaultColDef` (line 88-92), your custom properties will be combined with the defaults (resizable, sortable, comparator).

If you need to override for specific columns only, use `colDefOverrides`:

```tsx
<DataGridPanel
  meta={meta}
  data={data}
  colDefOverrides={[
    {
      field: "yourFieldName",
      colDef: {
        cellStyle: { 
          display: "flex", 
          justifyContent: "center", 
          alignItems: "center" 
        }
      }
    }
  ]}
/>
```

This is not working:
